 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Director, System Software Security NVIDIA 237 reviews Santa Clara, CA Remote NVIDIA 237 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description NVIDIA is looking for an outstanding Software Engineering Director to lead multiple dynamic and innovative teams in our Tegra System Software SoC group. This essential role will give you a rare opportunity to influence and deliver a wide range of products and functionality which impact all our growing businesses.
 You will help set and drive our security strategy and grow your teams both in size and skill. We need you to demonstrate a proven understanding of software development principles, and the willingness to work collaboratively and remotely with other teams to accomplish complex goals. You should have experience influencing decisions cross-organizationally and leading processes to meet multiple objectives. You should be passionate about finding opportunities for process improvements and automation.
 What you will be doing:
 As a security leader, you are expected to be both a technical and managerial leader for the Tegra System Software group, as well as leader more broadly throughout the company. You will be managing a team of outstanding security engineers and architects to build and deliver security and cryptographic features that are used in all Tegra-based SOC products across our automotive, enterprise, and embedded/IOT markets.
 Develop a strategic direction for investment and improvement of the secure architecture for multiple platforms in alignment with NVIDIA leadership.
 Continuously review and identify improvement opportunities in established processes, infrastructure and practices to ensure NVIDIA platforms are robust against current and future security threats.
 Provide direction and advice on emerging threats, vulnerabilities, and security practices that may have an impact on the security posture of the applicable environment.
 Cooperate with customers and partners to identify security challenges and craft a sound security solution which can serve long term and short-term business goals.
 What we need to see:
 15+ years working experience in embedded / SoC security industry, including 10+ years in a leadership position.
 5+ years' experience implementing defensive software security in products.
 BS, MS, or Ph.D. in CS, EE, CE (related technical field) or equivalent experience.
 Deep understanding of secure architecture and design fundamentals and their application in modern SoC's (System on a Chip), including root of trust, secure boot, and measured boot.
 Deep understanding and implementation experience with Public Key Cryptography Standards such as Cryptographic Token Interface, Elliptic Curve Cryptography
 Demonstrated ability to hire talented Software Engineers and establish elite engineering teams.
 Strong understanding of effective threat modeling, attack tree / pattern, and risk assessment skills.
 Sound knowledge of operating system architecture and security fundamentals such as UNIX based operating system, RTOS or microkernel.
 Hands-on skills with various programming languages including C, C++, Rust, Python and an understanding of how to use them for improving software security.
 Advanced problem-solving skills to identify complex security issues with software and hardware.
 The ability to work in a dynamic and diverse team is required and strong interpersonal skills and a real passion for working as a team are critical.
 Ways to stand out from the crowd:
 Familiar with ARMv8, ARMv9, and RISC-V architectures and related security fundamentals.
 Direct experience with server security systems and associated infrastructures.
 Experience with FIPS 140-2 and Common Criteria certification processes, including analysis of security requirements necessary to guide the development of security solutions that can attain Common Criterial EAL 5+ certification.
 Background with programming languages designed for safety and security such as Rust and the SPARK subset of Ada.
 Passion for taking the state-of-the-art in areas such as post-quantum cryptography and homomorphic encryption and building practical security solutions for problems that may not emerge for many years.
 Machine Learning, Deep-Learning, Artificial Intelligence experience as it relates to static code analysis and vulnerability.
